<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to General <persName type="to">Chou
                                    En-lai</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">OSE 126</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-06">June 6, 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear General Chou</hi>: The Generalissimo has
                            decided that he will not enter into a joint press release. Attached is
                            the release he proposes to give the press at noon today, Thursday, June
                                6th.<note n="98" xml:id="d510fn98"><hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi></note></p>
                        <p>In furnishing in advance this copy of the Generalissimo’s release I would
                            appreciate your giving me the opportunity to discuss with you the
                            proposed draft of your release, whatever it may be.<note n="99" xml:id="d510fn99"><p>Notation by General Marshall on June 6: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Gen Chou telephoned this a.m.</p>
                                        <list>
                                            <label>1.</label>
                                            <item>Regrets lack of joint statement</item>
                                            <label>2.</label>
                                            <item>Inclusion of statement regarding the taking over
                                                of sovereignty of Manchuria in Gimo statement</item>
                                            <label>3.</label>
                                            <item>He is drafting one—copy will be sent up later
                                                today.”</item>
                                        </list></quote></p>
                                <p>For latter, see press release of June 6, 4 p.m.
                                (below).</p></note></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>